ast deeds. Remember, O intelligent mind! Remember past deeds.Â 18.Â O divine Fire, knowing all our actions, lead us by the proper path for spiritual wealth (enlightenment). Purify us of our crooked offences. May we offer you countless reverent words of praise.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Â </p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span class=\"text-huge\" style=\"color:hsl(0, 0%, 0%);font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;\">OMÂ  Â That is perfect. This is perfect. Perfect comes from perfect. Take perfect from perfect, the remainder is perfect. OMÂ  Â peace, peace, peace.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Â </p><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"text-huge\" style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,0%);font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;\">ÄªÅ›Ä Upaniá¹£ad</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"text-huge\" style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,0%);font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Gaieaâ€™s artistic version using mantra 16, 1 â€“ 8 & 17</span></p><p>Â </p><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"text-huge\" style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,0%);font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;\">That which is - That Self - That I am. All this, anything that moves upon the earth, should be covered with that Self. Through such detachment you are protected and do not hanker after so-called possessions. Even if you wish to live here for a hundred years, dedicate all your actions to that Self. For a human being there is no other way not to get ensnared by action. But people who ignore that Self enter those devilish worlds death after death which are covered by blinding ignorance. The Self is one. Unmoving It runs ahead, faster than the mind; the senses can never reach It. Immovable, It outruns all other runners. That being there, air can support all of lifeâ€™s activities. Whoever sees all beings in himself and that Self in all beings, has no wish to despise anything. On seeing unity, when the Self alone has become all beings, what then is delusion? What is sor